File: rust/lichen-ipv6/src/lib.rs:383

In UdpHeader::write_to(), the length calculation can overflow:
```rust
let length = (UDP_HEADER_LEN + payload.len()) as u16;
```

If payload.len() > 65527 (65535 - 8), the cast to u16 will silently truncate, producing an incorrect length field. While unlikely in LoRa contexts (max ~250 bytes), this is a latent correctness bug that could cause issues if the module is reused in other contexts.

Fix: Add a check before the cast:
```rust
let total = UDP_HEADER_LEN + payload.len();
if total > u16::MAX as usize {
    return Err(BufferTooSmall::new(total, u16::MAX as usize).into());
}
let length = total as u16;
```
